PINOCCHIO
Pinocchio, a wooden puppet carved by Geppetto, dreamed of becoming a real boy. The Blue Fairy granted his wish, but on the condition that he proved himself brave, truthful, and unselfish. Along his journey, Pinocchio faced temptations and encountered characters like the sly fox and the conniving puppet master, Stromboli. Despite his struggles, Pinocchio showed bravery by rescuing Geppetto from the belly of a whale. In the end, his selfless act transformed him into a real boy, teaching the importance of honesty and kindness.
